        "adjustedEnd": "0:01:31.2",
        "start": "0:01:26.24",
        "end": "0:01:31.2"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 17,
    "text": "The initial plan was to build a 210 ish $1,000,000 arena starting in the fall of 2022 and finishing by the fall of 2025.",
    "confidence": 0.9057,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:01:31.56",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:01:38.52",
        "start": "0:01:31.56",
        "end": "0:01:38.52"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 18,
    "text": "What they actually did was sort of build a nearly $300 million arena starting in spring of 2023 and finishing.",
    "confidence": 0.8932,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:01:38.84",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:01:45",
        "start": "0:01:38.84",
        "end": "0:01:45"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 19,
    "text": "We all hope eventually for the Olympics the arena needed two things.",
    "confidence": 0.9358,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:01:45.16",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:01:49.64",
        "start": "0:01:45.16",
        "end": "0:01:49.64"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 20,
    "text": "One, to be a functional arena with places for spectators, press players, etcetera to sit, eat, go to the bathroom and generally be encased within walls and roof.",
    "confidence": 0.8857,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:01:49.84",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:01:58.08",
        "start": "0:01:49.84",
        "end": "0:01:58.08"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 21,
    "text": "And 2A game ready ice hockey rink, which is no easy task.",
    "confidence": 0.8945,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:01:58.4",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:02.8",
        "start": "0:01:58.4",
        "end": "0:02:02.8"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 22,
    "text": "You need to build a big concrete slab with pipes inside to circulate liquid cold enough to freeze water without itself freezing, which can maintain a consistent temperature across its entire surface.",
    "confidence": 0.9384,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:03.04",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:13",
        "start": "0:02:03.04",
        "end": "0:02:13"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 23,
    "text": "Then you got to mist down and freeze dozens of millimeter thick layers of ice to make sure you end up with an appropriately hard air bubble free hockey, safe sheet of ice.",
    "confidence": 0.8687,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:13.24",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:21.76",
        "start": "0:02:13.24",
        "end": "0:02:21.76"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 24,
    "text": "Building a decent rink is obviously important on its own, but even more so here because the National Hockey League, whose season the Winter Olympics lands smack in the middle of, is lending their players out to the Olympics and threatened that they pulled him out if the Santa Julia ice wasn't up to snuff.",
    "confidence": 0.8534,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:22.16",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:35.96",
        "start": "0:02:22.16",
        "end": "0:02:35.96"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 25,
    "text": "NHL have only been at 5 Olympics, with the most recent before 2026 being the 2014 Sochi Games.",
    "confidence": 0.8727,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:36.32",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:42.36",
        "start": "0:02:36.32",
        "end": "0:02:42.36"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 26,
    "text": "Since then, the NHL, the NHL players union, the international governing body of hockey, and the IOC couldn't come to an agreement that allowed NHL players to play.",
    "confidence": 0.9129,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:42.56",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:50.72",
        "start": "0:02:42.56",
        "end": "0:02:50.72"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 27,
    "text": "That's because letting them do so is, in many ways, not great for the league.",
    "confidence": 0.9741,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:51.08",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:54.84",
        "start": "0:02:51.08",
        "end": "0:02:54.84"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 28,
    "text": "The Olympics fall right in the middle of the regular NHL season and right after the end of the American football season, IE a great time to capture some wayward football fan eyeballs.",
    "confidence": 0.9339,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:55.2",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:04.76",
        "start": "0:02:55.2",
        "end": "0:03:04.76"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 29,
    "text": "In effectively leasing players to the Olympics, the NHL creates a huge gap in their schedule and takes on the risk that their best of the best players might get injured while they're there.",
    "confidence": 0.9337,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:05.16",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:13.4",
        "start": "0:03:05.16",
        "end": "0:03:13.4"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 30,
    "text": "Players that are being paid millions upon millions of dollars to play hockey in the NHL.",
    "confidence": 0.9675,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:13.6",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:18.64",
        "start": "0:03:13.6",
        "end": "0:03:18.64"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 31,
    "text": "So there's some hesitance to send their most valuable assets to Italy for three weeks.",
    "confidence": 0.8974,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:18.96",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:22.68",
        "start": "0:03:18.96",
        "end": "0:03:22.68"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 32,
    "text": "However, those valuable assets really vocally want to play for their national teams.",
    "confidence": 0.9067,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:23.04",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:27.88",
        "start": "0:03:23.04",
        "end": "0:03:27.88"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 33,
    "text": "Not to mention the Olympics fit nicely into the NHL stated desire to grow the game internationally.",
    "confidence": 0.8251,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:28",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:32.4",
        "start": "0:03:28",
        "end": "0:03:32.4"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 34,
    "text": "So with all that in mind, they reached an agreement for the Milan Olympics only to find out as of a few months before the 1st puck drop that the rank would be 3 feet shorter than they'd sign up for in the agreement.",
    "confidence": 0.8647,
    "speakerId": 1,
